      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "feat: add Orgo provider",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nAdds a direct delegated-run Orgo provider for Linux cloud computers.\n\n- Registers `provider: orgo` with alias `orgo-ai`.\n- Creates Orgo workspaces/computers through the REST API, runs commands through the bash endpoint, and deletes computers/workspaces during cleanup.\n- Keeps Orgo outside the coordinator broker and outside SSH/rsync flows; users must run with `--no-sync`.\n- Adds provider config, credential precedence, docs, generated provider metadata, unit tests, fake-API lifecycle coverage, and guarded live-smoke wiring.\n- Rebases onto current `main` and refreshes the generated provider matrix count.\n\n## Verification\n\nLocal validation on current head `a13a41ac2543af91594e6d6e84f96792c6864d9f`:\n\n```text\ngo test ./internal/providers/orgo ./internal/providers/all ./internal/cli ./cmd/crabbox\nnode --test scripts/live-smoke.test.js\nnode scripts/generate-provider-matrix.mjs --check\nnode scripts/check-command-docs.mjs\nnode scripts/check-docs-links.mjs\ngo vet ./...\ngo build -trimpath -o bin/crabbox ./cmd/crabbox\ngit diff --check\n```\n\nPublic CI is green on current head: https://github.com/openclaw/crabbox/actions/runs/28103708184\n\n## Security / Boundary Notes\n\n- API keys resolve from environment or trusted user config only; there is no API-key CLI flag.\n- Repository config cannot redirect an inherited Orgo API key to an arbitrary non-loopback API base.\n- Non-2xx Orgo response bodies are redacted before surfacing errors, including raw API-key echoes and `Bearer <key>` echoes.\n- Live-smoke wiring keeps the token out of argv and redacts forwarded environment from proof output.\n\n## Remaining Merge Gate\n\nDo not merge yet while `status: 📣 needs proof` and `merge-risk: 🚨 security-boundary` remain. This still needs redacted hosted Orgo lifecycle proof with real credentials: create workspace/computer, wait until running, execute command, delete computer/workspace, and show no leaked token/output.\n",
